152
00:09:56,050 --> 00:10:00,250
对不起 就谈一下
Oh,sorry,look,one word,all right.

153
00:10:00,570 --> 00:10:02,880
- 我们谈谈原则 - 原则?
- Principle. - Principle?

154
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:06,050
- 是啊 就谈原则 - 说吧
- Yeah,principle,okay. - Go on.

155
00:10:06,890 --> 00:10:09,200
- 我也是你们的一份子吧? - 是的
- I'm an equal partner. - Yeah.

156
00:10:09,370 --> 00:10:11,730
- 我说话也是算话的? - 当然
- I'm entitled to my say. - Absolutely.

157
00:10:11,810 --> 00:10:15,650
- 我跟你们是一样重要的吧? - 一样重要
- I got an equal voice. - Same as everyone else.

158
00:10:16,290 --> 00:10:20,680
我加入之前你们每个人都是认识的
Okay,you lot all knew each other before I come along,all right.

159
00:10:20,770 --> 00:10:24,050
但是我就是刚加入的
To me,it's like I'm on the outside looking in.

160
00:10:24,450 --> 00:10:27,330
- Danny. - 就是说
- Oh,Danny. - Yeah,it's like...

161
00:10:27,690 --> 00:10:31,690
我当时也是个外人吧
the kid with the nose pressed up against the window.

162
00:10:31,770 --> 00:10:34,570
还是在说原则问题吧?
So this,it's all a matter of principle,yeah?

163
00:10:34,650 --> 00:10:36,610
是吧 Ash 不就是因为我能帮上忙吗?
That's it,Ash,principle.Yeah.

164
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:39,970
我说了我会担保他的 我想 我说话
I said I'd vouch for the bloke,didn't I?I mean,I think my word...

165
00:10:40,170 --> 00:10:44,050
还是能当一回事的吧 如果你连我都不信
should be vouchable.And if it's not,then....

166
00:10:45,810 --> 00:10:49,520
如果真是那样 我只能走了 咱们拆伙好了
I guess what I'm saying is,if it's not,then I'm gonna have to walk.

167
00:10:52,410 --> 00:10:53,770
我说完了
There you go,I've said it now.

168
00:10:53,850 --> 00:10:56,730
我的意思是
I mean,sometimes a bloke has to stand up for...

169
00:10:58,130 --> 00:10:59,930
用人不疑 疑人不用吧
what he stands for.

170
00:11:07,250 --> 00:11:10,640
他说的有道理 他毕竟是我们的拍档 怎么也该相信他
He has a point.A little trust goes a long way.

171
00:11:10,730 --> 00:11:13,770
好的 但是我们还不清楚他底细
Yeah,but we don't know him.

172
00:11:14,690 --> 00:11:17,650
我们当初要Danny来帮忙的时候 还不是不清楚他的底细?
Well,we didn't know Danny when we took him on.

173
00:11:25,850 --> 00:11:26,890
好的
Okay.

174
00:11:28,450 --> 00:11:29,520
Danny
Danny.

175
00:11:37,570 --> 00:11:40,090
我们给他次机会
Okay,we're gonna give him a chance on this one job.

176
00:11:40,170 --> 00:11:42,450
如果第一次就搞砸了 他就走人
The first time he screws up,he's out.

177
00:11:42,570 --> 00:11:45,250
干杯 谢谢 你们不会后悔的
Cheers,thanks,you won't regret it.

178
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:49,440
我当时没给你面子 我不是故意的
I didn't mean what I said and sorry about burping in your face.

179
00:11:49,610 --> 00:11:50,600
爱死你们了
Love you all.

180
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:02,880
- 那Mgube的买卖怎么下手? - 就投其所好好了
- So,how do we get to this Mgube? - His hobby.

181
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:06,440
他出名爱收集古董钞票
He has a world-renowned collection of rare banknotes.

182
00:12:06,530 --> 00:12:08,760
他身家丰厚
Yeah,he looks like he's worth a few quid.

183
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:12,450
有人估算过 他身家大概有6亿美元
Last time,it was estimated at $60 million.

184
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:16,010
- 那有多少个0啊 - 好多个罗
- How many noughts is that,then? - Lots.

185
00:12:16,450 --> 00:12:17,600
那要怎么下手
And the way in?

186
00:12:17,690 --> 00:12:20,690
他很想要找的一张古钞
He's desperate to add one new note to his collection.

187
00:12:21,330 --> 00:12:24,050
叫Yankee Green
Yankee Green known because...

188
00:12:24,130 --> 00:12:25,250
怎会有这名字 因为是绿色的?
It's green?

189
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:30,040
是的 就是绿色的 那是以前用造钞工艺 现在已经失传了
Extremely so,yes.It was a new color process that did not catch on.

190
00:12:30,130 --> 00:12:33,210
就因为这 它也身价百倍
But that in itself adds to its value.

191
00:12:33,290 --> 00:12:38,240
那是一张面值$1,000的钞票 1866年发行
It's a $1,000 treasury note issued in 1866.

192
00:12:38,770 --> 00:12:41,330
上面有George Gordon Meade将军的头像...
The head is of General George Gordon Meade...

193
00:12:41,410 --> 00:12:45,480
联邦军队指挥官的葛底斯堡战役
Commander of the Union Forces at the Battle of Gettysburg.

194
00:12:45,610 --> 00:12:47,410
那东西值多少钱?
How much is something like that worth,then?

195
00:12:47,490 --> 00:12:49,610
全世界只剩两张了
Only two are known to still be in existence.

196
00:12:49,690 --> 00:12:52,410
芝加哥联合银行买下了一张
One is owned by the Chicago Confederate Bank...

197
00:12:52,490 --> 00:12:56,810
9年前买的 花了$200,000英镑
for which they paid $200,000 nine years ago.

198
00:12:56,970 --> 00:13:00,600
我想Mgube一直也要买但是没买成吧
And I take it that Mgube has offered to buy it and been turned down?

199
00:13:00,690 --> 00:13:02,250
他的确一直想买到它
Frequently,yes.

200
00:13:02,450 --> 00:13:04,010
那我们有什么法子?
So,where do we come in?

201
00:13:04,290 --> 00:13:05,930
还有第二张
Now,the second note....

202
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:09,170
很少人知道它在哪
Only a handful of people know its whereabouts.

203
00:13:09,410 --> 00:13:11,090
总算被我找到了
Fortunately,I'm one of them.

204
00:13:11,410 --> 00:13:14,640
给它作保险的那家公司的CEO是我的朋友
The CEO of the company that insures it is a friend of mine.

205
00:13:14,810 --> 00:13:16,960
你朋友还真多
Everyone's a friend of yours,Albie.

206
00:13:18,090 --> 00:13:21,130
它现在在Anne Foster手上
The owner of the note is Anne Foster.

207
00:13:21,810 --> 00:13:24,330
是他第二任丈夫留给她的遗物
It is kept in her late husband's collection.

208
00:13:24,410 --> 00:13:26,850
Mgube还不知道这事吗?
But Mgube doesn't know anything about her?

209
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:29,160
他只知道第二张钞票被私人收藏了
He knows the second note belongs to a private collector...

210
00:13:29,250 --> 00:13:31,320
但他找不到那收藏家
he just hasn't been able to track it down.

211
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:34,880
就算他找到了Foster 她也说过她不想把钞票卖掉
Even if he did,she's made it clear that she will never sell it.

212
00:13:35,290 --> 00:13:39,130
好的 那么有个百万富翁想找一样 东西而我们又知道那东西在哪
Okay,so we got a millionaire who wants something and we know where it is.

213
00:13:39,770 --> 00:13:42,370
- 那 又怎样呢 - 我们去偷吧
- Now,what? - Can't we just nick it?

214
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:48,210
我们能伪造一张吗?
Can we forge the note?

215
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:52,000
能是能 但是Mgube可能连钞票的序列号都知道
Possible.But chances are Mgube knows the serial number.

216
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:55,050
我们得先去看看那张真的
We'll need to see the real one.

217
00:13:55,210 --> 00:13:59,000
- 就是说? - 我们要找到Foster看看那张真的
- Which means? - Getting close enough to the original.

218
00:14:07,730 --> 00:14:08,880
Foster?
Mrs.Foster?

219
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:15,490
没什么事 我们只是想对你在我们 公司投保的几件贵重物品
No,it's nothing serious,Mrs.Foster,we'd simply like to update our assessment...

220
00:14:15,570 --> 00:14:19,930
更新一下评估
on some of the more valuable items that we insure.

221
00:14:20,450 --> 00:14:23,970
- 不是已经更新过了吗 - 不
- My premiums are up to date,you know. - No.

222
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:27,090
手续上还要再确认一次
No,it's more a case of making sure...

223
00:14:27,290 --> 00:14:30,600
确保那些物品的状况
that some of the items are in the same condition as...

224
00:14:30,690 --> 00:14:32,760
还有担保的价值
when the insurance was taken out.

225
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:35,010
我83岁了
I'm 83,you know.

226
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:38,370
不是吧 你看上去就像75岁
I don't believe that.You don't look a day over 75.

227
00:14:39,290 --> 00:14:41,170
你还要蛋糕吗?
Would you like another slice of cake?

228
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:44,770
不要了谢谢 好了 我们开始
Maybe later.Anyway,moving on.

229
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:48,450
首饰 好的 应该没问题
Right,jewelry,that should be fine.

230
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:53,360
- 这上面写你还有些旧钞 - 是我死了的丈夫的
- I see here you have some banknotes. - My late husband's.

231
00:14:53,730 --> 00:14:55,920
知道了 好的
Right,okay.

232
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:59,000
对这些宝贝可要千万小心
Always a danger of damp with those.

233
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:01,050
我把它们放在个密室里了
They're in a sealed cabinet.

234
00:15:02,570 --> 00:15:04,170
可以让我们看一下吗?
Do you mind if we have a look?

235
00:15:06,410 --> 00:15:09,050
我们还要准备一点东西
There are a few more things we need for the Mgube con.

236
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:11,400
只是好像我们的流动资金不足
But it seems we're short of working capital.

237
00:15:11,490 --> 00:15:13,050
于是我就想...
And then I thought to myself...

238
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:15,250
我能叫谁帮忙呢?
who do I know who could solve a problem like that?

239
00:15:15,330 --> 00:15:17,690
- 我们还缺些什么 - 这是清单
- What do we need? - I've got a list.

240
00:15:23,570 --> 00:15:25,930
行了 不算太多拉
Cor blimey,you don't want much,do you?

241
00:15:26,770 --> 00:15:28,730
- 我留着吧 - 好的
- Leave it with me. - Okay.

242
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:47,370
你在我们酒店过得愉快吗 先生?
Was everything all right with your stay,sir?

243
00:15:57,770 --> 00:16:00,080
请在这签名
If you'd just like to sign at the bottom for me.

244
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:09,520
谢谢
Thank you.

245
00:16:17,170 --> 00:16:18,290
你好 来克星顿酒店
The Lexington.

246
00:16:18,370 --> 00:16:20,650
这是信用卡中心
This is Credit Card Authorization.

247
00:16:20,730 --> 00:16:23,250
你们遇到我们授权的问题吗?
I understand you've got an authorization problem.

248
00:16:23,330 --> 00:16:26,640
- 没事啊 一切正常吧 - 是吗 刚刚我屏幕显示你们这有问题的喔
- Well,everything looks fine here. - It's just showed up on me screen.

249
00:16:26,730 --> 00:16:29,330
- 我不知道什么回事 - 我来问你
- I don't know why that is. - I tell you what's happened.

250
00:16:29,410 --> 00:16:32,450
- 你刚有进行信用卡交易吗? - 是的 有啊
- Did you just do a card transaction? - Yes,a credit card.

251
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:34,680
是吗 可能就是这桩交易出问题了
You did?Yeah,well,it may not have gone through.

252
00:16:34,770 --> 00:16:36,760
你能提供那信用卡号 让我查一下吧
Do you wanna give me the card number so I can check it?

253
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:39,930
好的 号码是 4628
Sure,the number is 4628....

254
00:16:40,970 --> 00:16:44,170
你好 我要用信用卡购物
Yeah,I'd like to make a credit card purchase,please.

255
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:57,290
好的
Okay.

256
00:17:06,610 --> 00:17:07,970
镊子
Tweezers.

257
00:17:18,210 --> 00:17:19,330
好
Yeah.

258
00:17:22,690 --> 00:17:24,330
有什么问题吗?
Is something wrong?

259
00:17:24,890 --> 00:17:27,330
可能没有吧
Probably not....

260
00:17:27,850 --> 00:17:31,050
我想我们要照些照片
I think we may have to take some photographs...

261
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:33,850
用来更新我们的资料 可以吗?
just to update our files,if that's okay?

262
00:17:34,490 --> 00:17:36,800
你们需要就照好了
You must do whatever you think best.

263
00:17:48,730 --> 00:17:49,930
Yankee Green
Yankee Green.

264
00:17:50,130 --> 00:17:53,050
- 你能仿造吗 - 那种纸可能难找一点
- Can you do it? - Paper might be difficult.

265
00:17:53,130 --> 00:17:55,930
- 那水印呢? - 那个没问题
- What about the seal? - No,I can do that.

266
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:59,170
- 要给谁? - 给一个收藏家的
- Who does it have to pass? - A collector.

267
00:17:59,770 --> 00:18:02,290
- 要送到实验室做测试吗? - 不 应该不用的
- Lab tests? - No,hopefully not.

268
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:07,610
- 能做好吗? - Stone先生 有钱可是能使鬼推磨啊
- Is it doable? - Everything's doable,Mr.Stone.

269
00:18:08,090 --> 00:18:10,650
好的
- At a price. - Right.

270
00:18:19,290 --> 00:18:22,090
现在先付一半 事成之后再付清
Half now,half when it's done.

271
00:18:23,410 --> 00:18:26,450
但是我已经储钱进我的帐户了
But I've paid money into the account now,so...

272
00:18:26,610 --> 00:18:28,920
你还不能扣清我的贷款额吗?
couldn't you just take off the charges?

273
00:18:30,170 --> 00:18:33,850
为什么?因为客人是上帝啊
A reason?Well,how about customer service?

274
00:18:34,010 --> 00:18:37,480
再说 这样做也合情合理啊
Or just plain,old-fashioned bloody courtesy?

275
00:18:38,610 --> 00:18:42,290
我不是说骂你 我是想说
I am not swearing at you,I'm just trying to point out...

276
00:18:42,370 --> 00:18:46,050
你真他妈的臭男人长着个猪脑子啊?
that you're an arrogant little man with a brain the size of a pea.

277
00:18:49,650 --> 00:18:52,120
喂 喂
Hello?Hello?

278
00:18:53,570 --> 00:18:56,880
- 他挂电话了 - 他真是没礼貌啊
- He hung up. - I can't think why.

279
00:18:57,130 --> 00:18:58,850
好 这么不给我面子
Right,this means war.

280
00:18:59,650 --> 00:19:03,250
不就是85英镑吗 这有点小题大做了吧
It's 85,my dear.Isn't war a little overzealous?

281
00:19:03,330 --> 00:19:04,730
这是原则问题
It's the principle.

282
00:19:05,810 --> 00:19:09,690
又是原则 现在都流行讲原则啊
Principle again.It seems to be the word of the moment.

283
00:19:10,490 --> 00:19:12,800
- 穿上衣服 Albie. - 干什么?
- Get your coat,Albie. - Why?

284
00:19:13,050 --> 00:19:15,040
我们要动手了
Because we are gonna get him.

285
00:19:15,410 --> 00:19:17,450
- 整他? - 那个叫Hopkins的
- Get him? - Hopkins.

286
00:19:17,530 --> 00:19:21,810
他见过我 所以我不能去 不过你可以帮我
Yep,he knows me but you can be my secret weapon.Come on.

287
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:33,290
对不起Reeves小姐 我们处理办法不复杂
Look,be that as it may,Mrs.Reeves,we have a very simple system here.

288
00:19:33,370 --> 00:19:35,930
我简单给你说一下
Let me unscramble the intricacies of it for you.

289
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:38,890
你帐户有钱 你才能取钱出来
If you have money in your account,you can take it out.

290
00:19:39,050 --> 00:19:41,490
- 但是你没有 - 孩子 走吧
- You haven't. - Come on,kids.

291
00:19:44,530 --> 00:19:47,050
Hopkins?我叫Harrison Wyngate
Mr.Hopkins?Harrison Wyngate.

292
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:48,410
- 请进 - 谢谢
- Please. - Thank you.

293
00:19:48,490 --> 00:19:50,050
- 让我来开 - 好的
- Let me. - Fine.

294
00:19:51,770 --> 00:19:53,920
好的 下一步 要对付了Mgube
Okay,next step,Mgube.

295
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:56,530
我们跟他租车的公司有联络
We've got a contact in the limousine company he's using...

296
00:19:56,610 --> 00:20:00,000
所以我们知道他今天下午会到Strand 的一家古董钞票商那去
so we know he's due to visit the banknote dealers in the Strand this afternoon.

297
00:20:00,090 --> 00:20:02,730
- 我们能搞好的 对吧 Trev? - 对
- We can do that,can't we,Trev? - Yeah.

298
00:20:03,130 --> 00:20:05,890
他今天对付那老太太的时候出色极了
He did really good today,Mick,with the old girl.

299
00:20:07,290 --> 00:20:11,490
- 你跟人合伙骗过人吗? - 我只是听说过
- Have you ever worked on a long con? - I've read about it.

300
00:20:11,770 --> 00:20:15,610
行了 好了 我去办这事 他给我做帮手得了
Yeah,well,I'll make the play,he'll just back me up.

301
00:20:15,690 --> 00:20:17,210
那你还不如带上Ash
I'd rather you took Ash.

302
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:21,680
好的 Mick 你是老板 当然你说了算
All right,Mick,you're the boss,it's your call,but....

303
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:27,720
要不是有人教我 我也不会有今天啊
I mean,I wouldn't be sitting here,would I,if somebody hadn't taught me?

304
00:20:34,490 --> 00:20:36,770
别把事搞砸了
Do not louse this up.

305
00:20:36,850 --> 00:20:38,570
我们不会的
No,we won't.

306
00:20:44,130 --> 00:20:47,600
要转帐是没问题的 你有在这开过户吗?
Setting up a transfer is no problem.Do you have an account here?

307
00:20:47,730 --> 00:20:50,930
没有 外面的小姐给了我一张表格要我填
No,not yet but the young lady out there gave me the forms to fill out.

308
00:20:51,010 --> 00:20:54,160
我们批准你的申请之后 就会把银行帐号给你
Once your application has been processed we can give you an account number...

309
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:55,730
到时你就可以转帐了
so you can arrange the transaction.

310
00:20:55,810 --> 00:20:57,330
你打算要转帐多少钱呢?
Do you know how much you'll be transferring?

311
00:20:57,410 --> 00:20:58,810
3百万
3 million,yes.

312
00:20:59,930 --> 00:21:02,970
- 不好意思? - 这是启动基金
- Excuse me? - That's just the first installment.

313
00:21:03,090 --> 00:21:05,400
- 启动基金? - 我所代表的公司
- First? - Yes,the company I represent...

